{
 "name": "RPlog_Futile_Research_-_Runaway",
 "title": "Futile Research: Runaway",
 "summary": "Late at night in a Coruscant starport, the New Republic Marine Sandor Woden -- adrift and haunted after Cochran -- nearly collides with the refugee girl Arise, who is hurrying with grim determination toward a banking terminal. When her credit chit fails because of a Parental Consent Override, Sandor, mistaking her for a lost child or pickpocket, follows and learns she is trying to reach the Cochran refugees. He gently breaks the news that the survivors fled to Calamari, dissuades her from running off to a planet of strangers, and even offers his own credits, which Arise politely refuses. Their exchange is interrupted by new arrivals at the starport: the red-haired Taria descending the Bad Seed, the disillusioned pilot Dias Winter ripping the New Republic insignia from his uniform and grinding it underfoot, and Krieg searching the crowd for a friend. Defeated, Arise finally resigns herself to returning to the very government refugee program she despises, while Sandor is left to brood over his own powerlessness.",
